---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
	title="Email (SMTP)"
	description="Send email notifications via MailChannels or Resend HTTP gateway using notifly."
	section="Services"
	prev={{ title: 'Pushbullet', href: '/docs/services/pushbullet' }}
	next={{ title: 'Webhook (Generic)', href: '/docs/services/webhook' }}
>
	<h1>Email</h1>
	<p>
		Send email notifications via an HTTP email gateway. Raw SMTP is not supported in Web API
		environments, so notifly uses gateways: <strong>MailChannels</strong> (free on Cloudflare Workers)
		or <strong>Resend</strong> (free tier available).
	</p>

	<h2>URL format</h2>
	<CodeBlock
		code="mailto://user:gateway@host?to=recipient@example.com[&api_key=xxx][&from=sender@domain]"
		lang="text"
		label="scheme"
	/>

	<table>
		<thead>
			<tr>
				<th>Field</th>
				<th>Required</th>
				<th>Description</th>
			</tr>
		</thead>
		<tbody>
			<tr>
				<td><code>to</code></td>
				<td>Yes</td>
				<td>Recipient email address</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><code>gateway</code></td>
				<td>Yes</td>
				<td><code>mailchannels</code> or <code>resend</code></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><code>user</code></td>
				<td>No</td>
				<td>Sender username (local part of From address)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><code>host</code></td>
				<td>No</td>
				<td>Sender domain</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><code>api_key</code></td>
				<td>Resend only</td>
				<td>Your Resend API key</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><code>from</code></td>
				<td>No</td>
				<td>Full sender email address (overrides user@host)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><code>cc</code></td>
				<td>No</td>
				<td>CC recipient</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td><code>bcc</code></td>
				<td>No</td>
				<td>BCC recipient</td>
			</tr>
		</tbody>
	</table>

	<h2>MailChannels example (Cloudflare Workers)</h2>
	<CodeBlock
		code={`import { notify } from '@ambersecurityinc/notifly';

await notify(
  {
    urls: [
      'mailto://alerts:mailchannels@mycompany.com?to=team@mycompany.com'
    ],
  },
  { title: 'Deploy Alert', body: 'Production deploy completed', type: 'success' }
);`}
		lang="typescript"
	/>

	<h2>Resend example</h2>
	<CodeBlock
		code={`await notify(
  {
    urls: [
      'mailto://alerts:resend@mycompany.com?to=team@mycompany.com&api_key=re_xxxxxxxxxx'
    ],
  },
  { title: 'Alert', body: 'Something happened', type: 'warning' }
);`}
		lang="typescript"
	/>

	<h2>Getting credentials</h2>
	<h3>MailChannels</h3>
	<p>
		MailChannels is available for free on Cloudflare Workers with no additional configuration — it's
		baked into the Cloudflare network. See the <a href="/docs/guides/cloudflare-workers"
			>Cloudflare Workers guide</a
		> for setup details.
	</p>

	<h3>Resend</h3>
	<ol>
		<li>Sign up at <a href="https://resend.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">resend.com</a>.</li>
		<li>Go to <strong>API Keys</strong> → <strong>Create API Key</strong>.</li>
		<li>Add your sending domain and verify DNS records.</li>
		<li>Copy the API key (starts with <code>re_</code>).</li>
	</ol>

	<h2>Quirks &amp; limitations</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Raw SMTP (ports 25/465/587) is blocked in most serverless environments.</li>
		<li>MailChannels only works from Cloudflare Workers networks.</li>
		<li>Resend requires a verified sending domain for production use.</li>
	</ul>
</DocsLayout>
